<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-663-743  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 663 743.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>ACM Transactions on Programming Languages andamp; Systems  Oct 1990 v12n4 p566(44).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>An approach to support automatic generation of user interfaces.andO;(technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Dewan, Prasun; Solomon, Marvin.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Automatic generation of user interfaces can correct the three mainproblems in traditional interactive programming environments: thehigh cost of implementing user interfaces, inconsistent modes ofinteraction, and being primitive because they do not offer severalhard to implement features.andP;  Automatic generation of userinterfaces requires the design of an application-independent modelof interaction with an environment that supports the model.andP;  Theediting model of interaction is supported by the approachpresented.andP;  The approach, which is tailored to Pascal-likelanguages, automates input and output of values ofprogrammer-defined types, has conventional programming languagesas its base, permits the user to interact with severalapplications simultaneously, and permits an implementor to use asingle description of the data structures for display, entry,modification and semantic processing.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     PASCALUser InterfaceSoftware EngineeringEditingObject Code.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Editing a directory. (chart)Creating a bibliography. (chart)Editing a bibliography. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>